inlineContent.text: The closure returns no value and takes the following parameters:
The change token to store and use in subsequent instances of
The more recent client change token from the device. If the change token isn’t the more recent change token you provided, the server might not have received the associated changes.
A Boolean that indicates whether this is the final record zone change. If
, it’s the app’s responsibility to create additional instances of
An error object that contains information about a problem, or
if the operation successfully retrieves the results.
The app is responsible for saving the change token at the end of the operation and providing it to future uses of
. Each time the closure executes, it executes serially with respect to the other closures of the operation.
Set this property before you execute the operation or submit it to a queue.
